# ============================================================
# InvoiceFlow — multi-stack .gitignore
# Stacks: .NET (src/, tests/, packages/) · Next.js (frontend/) ·
#         Python FastAPI (backend/, alembic/) · Docker compose
# ============================================================

# ---------------- .NET / C# ----------------
# Build outputs (NOTE: `bin/` and `obj/` are listed AGAIN after the NuGet section
# because gitignore uses "last match wins" — a later pattern overrides an earlier
# one, so the `!packages/InvoiceFlow.X/**` re-includes must not swallow bin/obj
# for files inside those source projects).
*.user
*.userosscache
*.suo
*.userprefs
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
x64/
x86/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*
*.[Pp]ublish.xml
*.pfx
*.snupkg
AppPackages/
BundleArtifacts/
.vs/

# Test & coverage
TestResults/
[Cc]overage/
*.coverage
coverage*.xml

# NuGet — `packages/` is MIXED in this repo. Two kinds of children:
#   Source projects (KEEP):    packages/InvoiceFlow.*  (5 C# class-library projects)
#   NuGet restore cache (IGNORE): packages/<lowercase-package-id>/<version>/  (auto-generated by `dotnet restore`)
# IMPORTANT: a bare `packages/` excludes the parent dir, and gitignore spec says
# a file cannot be re-included when its parent is excluded — so we MUST use a glob
# (`packages/**`) and re-include each source dir explicitly with `/**` so git
# descends and tracks contents.
packages/**
!packages/InvoiceFlow.Compliance.Abstractions/**
!packages/InvoiceFlow.Cryptography/**
!packages/InvoiceFlow.DocumentParser/**
!packages/InvoiceFlow.EventBus/**
!packages/InvoiceFlow.Formats.Abstractions/**

# Build artifacts — placed HERE (AFTER the `!packages/InvoiceFlow.X/**` re-includes
# above) so the gitignore "last match wins" rule excludes bin/obj even for files
# inside the re-included InvoiceFlow.* source projects (their build outputs must
# never leak into git).
bin/
obj/

*.nupkg
*.snupkg
.nuget/

# Visual Studio / Rider
*.sln.docstates
*.VisualState.xml
*.csproj.user
*.swp

